<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="270" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1779,2020]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1779,1804]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">Diagnosis</emphasis>
(modified from 
<bibRefCitation author="Pleijel" box="[459,712,1779,1804]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" refString="Pleijel, F. &amp; Rouse, G. W. (2005) A revision of Micropodarke (Psamathini, Hesionidae, Polychaeta). Journal of Natural History, 39, 1313 - 1325. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930400020129" type="journal article" year="2005">
Pleijel &amp; Rouse 
<number box="[651,712,1779,1804]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Presence of proboscis diaphragm, segmental ventral adhesive papillae, distally knobbed, and slightly curved neuroaciculae, and three to six median neurochaetae with few, basally situated prolonged teeth (“spurs”), with abrupt transition to following, much shorter teeth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="271" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1779,2020]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1436,151,392]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="271" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1887,1912]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[322,481,1888,1912]" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Micropodarke" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[322,481,1888,1912]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">Micropodarke</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is regarded as a monotypic genus. 
<bibRefCitation author="Okuda" box="[874,1030,1887,1912]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" refString="Okuda, S. (1938) Polychaetous annelids from the vicinity of the Mitsui Institute of Marine Biology. Japanese Journal of Zoology, 8, 75 - 105." type="journal article" year="1938">
Okuda (
<number box="[963,1021,1888,1912]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" value="1938.0">1938</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName box="[1151,1297,1888,1912]" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Micropodarke" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="amemiyai">
<emphasis box="[1151,1297,1888,1912]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">M. amemiyai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on an incomplete specimen (
<quantity box="[408,490,1924,1948]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
long, 
<number box="[564,592,1923,1948]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" value="50.0">50</number>
chaetigers), collected near Mitsui, Izu Peninsula, 
<collectingCountry box="[1166,1233,1924,1947]" name="Japan" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">Japan</collectingCountry>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[1298,1346,1924,1948]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">type</typeStatus>
species was regarded as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Hessle, 1925" authorityName="Hessle" authorityYear="1925" box="[574,848,1959,1984]" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Micropodarke" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="dubia">
<emphasis box="[574,676,1960,1984]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">M. dubia</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hessle" box="[692,839,1959,1984]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" refString="Hessle, C. (1925) Einiges uber die Hesioniden und die Stellung der Gattung Ancistrosyllis. Arkiv for Zoologi, 17 A, 1 - 36." type="journal article" year="1925">
Hessle, 
<number box="[782,839,1959,1984]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" value="1925.0">1925</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Imajima" box="[891,1202,1959,1984]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" refString="Imajima, M. &amp; Hartman, O. (1964) The Polychaetous Annelids of Japan, Part 2. Allan Hancock Foundation Occasional Papers, 26, 239 - 452." type="journal article" year="1964">
Imajima &amp; Hartman (
<number box="[1135,1193,1959,1984]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" value="1964.0">1964</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Pleijel" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" refString="Pleijel, F. &amp; Rouse, G. W. (2005) A revision of Micropodarke (Psamathini, Hesionidae, Polychaeta). Journal of Natural History, 39, 1313 - 1325. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930400020129" type="journal article" year="2005">
Pleijel &amp; Rouse (
<number box="[159,220,1995,2020]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" value="2005.0">2005</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Hartmann-Schroder, 1983" authorityName="Hartmann-Schroder" authorityYear="1983" box="[290,728,1995,2020]" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Micropodarke" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="trilobata">
<emphasis box="[290,428,1996,2020]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">M. trilobata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hartmann-Schroder" box="[435,728,1995,2020]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" refString="Hartmann-Schroder, G. (1983) Die Polychaeten der antiborealen Sudkuste Australiens (zwischen Albany im Westen und Ceduna im Osten). Teil 10. In: Hartmann-Schroder, G. and Gerd Hartmann. Zur Kenntnis des Eulitorals der australischen Kusten unter besonderer Berucksichtigung der Polychaeten und Ostracoden. Mitteilungen aus dem Hamburgischen zoologischen Museum und Institut, 81, 7 - 62." type="journal article" year="1983">
Hartmann-Schröder, 
<number box="[672,728,1996,2020]" pageId="3" pageNumber="270" value="1983.0">1983</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[799,905,1995,2020]" name="Australia" pageId="3" pageNumber="270">Australia</collectingCountry>
, also described with an anterior fragment, was also synonymized with 
<taxonomicName box="[442,552,152,176]" class="Polychaeta" family="Hesionidae" genus="Micropodarke" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="dubia">
<emphasis box="[442,552,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="271">M. dubia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pleijel" box="[612,900,151,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" refString="Pleijel, F. &amp; Rouse, G. W. (2005) A revision of Micropodarke (Psamathini, Hesionidae, Polychaeta). Journal of Natural History, 39, 1313 - 1325. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930400020129" type="journal article" year="2005">
Pleijel &amp; Rouse (
<number box="[830,891,151,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="271" value="2005.0">2005</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. There are some differences in the relative development of ciliary bands in the first segments, relative size of antennae and palps (some specimens have them of about the same length), and of adhesive glands (some specimens having them as short lobes with blunt, hemispherical tips against others with a projected lobe with conical, blunt tip). The identity of this supposedly widely distributed species must be evaluated with molecular methods and with the study of living specimens to clarify their pigmentation patterns. The following key is based upon the morphological features indicated above and other features.
</paragraph>
